How to get the full container id in docker - var=`docker ps -a --no-trunc | grep <imagename> | awk '{print $1}'`
To get Real time logs - docker logs --option containerid
To get the stats of Docker containers - sudo docker stats --no-stream
For Removing Docker - sudo dnf remove -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io 
Enable the Docker container - sudo systemctl enable docker 
Start Docker Container - sudo systemctl start docker 
Removing Data which are prune - sudo docker system prune -a -f
For Docker daemon debug - sudo dockerd --debug
Stop all running containers: docker stop $(docker ps -a -q)
Delete all stopped containers: docker rm $(docker ps -a -q)
docker commit : Create a new Image from a container changes
